HEADWORD: Corbeil
<hw>Cor"beil</hw> <pr>(k⟦ocir⟧r"b⟦ecr⟧l)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>corbeille</ets>, fr. L. <ets>corbicula</ets> a little basket, dim.
of <ets>corbis</ets> basket. Cf. <er>Corbel</er>, <er>Corb</er>,
<er>Corvette</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Arch.)</fld> <def>A
sculptured basket of flowers; a corbel.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <pluf>pl.</pluf> <fld>(Fort.)</fld> <def>Small
